				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Don't charm Eldrig<a name="33402"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 7 04 2:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Folks I wrote an in-depth guide for this a long time ago<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />for all you peoples who want a method to do this in your 50's (like i did)
<br />

<br />
http://eqdiva.com/EQ/Guide.aspx?id=44&amp;ForumID=132
<br />

<br />
or pasted here:
<br />

<br />
Kill Eldrig the Old (the easy way)
<br />

<br />
Well actually there are two easy ways. 
<br />

<br />
First way: 
<br />

<br />
SONGS TO HAVE UP FOR THIS METHOD: 
<br />
--Song of travel and/or Clouding (inviz) 
<br />
--Snare just to pull 
<br />
--Song of dawn (hit him with it as you approach the group killing him so he drops off of you quickly) 
<br />
--Selo's accelerating chorus 
<br />
--the rest dont really matter that much. 
<br />

<br />
Since Ragefire was moved to Skyfire, there are always people there farming shards. Ask a group there if you can pull eldrig to them. Just dont do any damage to him during your pull as he will summon you to death. This is how I got my Eldrig guts. I actually pulled Eldrig clear across the zone w/o any adds. pull and use selo's song of travel or clouding and stay a good distance away to avoid the dispell/dot and nothing will ever agro. Get the loc of the group your are pulling to, kill, loot. easy. 
<br />

<br />
pulling tip: If you get an add, snare it, but dont snare Eldrig. You'll run out of range and lose agro, keeping Eldrig in agro range. 
<br />

<br />
Second way: (the most fun way) 
<br />

<br />
SONGS TO HAVE UP FOR THIS METHOD: 
<br />
--Solon's Bewitching Bravura 
<br />
--Chorus of Replinishment or your best song in this line 
<br />
--Niv's Melody of Preservation (or Breath of Harmony if you are rich enough or got lucky in seb) 
<br />
--Angstlich's Appalling Screech (fear) 
<br />
--Selo's Accelerating Chorus 
<br />
--Shauri's Sonorous Clouding 
<br />
--The rest is really up to you. 
<br />

<br />
If there are no groups there, or you just want to have fun, do it this way. Pull Eldrig with a non damage song to the Druid ring (sorta near Burning woods zone). Try to stay out of range of Eldrig's dispell / DoT if you can. If not, no biggie. Find a NON CHROMODRAKE type mob (wurms are good) and pull it to the zone wall where there are no adds. (this area is between the BW zone and the druid port in) Equip a wind instrument and charm Eldrig. Yes i know your are saying &quot;WTF Ash? Charm Eldrig? but he summons!&quot; but charm him...and sic him on the NON CHROMODRAKE mobs. The reason I say NON CHROMODRAKE is because the Chromodrakes will dispell your charm from Eldrig every 5 seconds or so. Have Eldrig kill the wurm or whatever agroes. As soon as charm breaks, you WILL get summoned. Run out of melee range and recharm. Park Eldrig there and go get another mob. While Eldrig kills your pull, switch to strings and twist your 2 regens. You'll gain HP back even if Eldrig has DoT'd you with boil blood. Wash rinse repeat until Eldrig is about at 2 or 3 percent health. Then proceed to fear kite him dead. 
<br />

<br />
This method is much faster than fear kiting him for 30 minutes straight. GAH. whoever first suggested that should be hung by their toenails and beaten with a wet noodle. After 2 mins of fear kiting him down from 2% GRATS, you've got your guts and had a d*mn fun time soloing Eldrig. 
<br />

<br />
An alternitive to fear kiting is to bring any nuker and just finish him off after the last mob is dead.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
